Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer 35-43 Pauljoseph Way, Truganina, for lease. 

Melbourneâ€™s Western region has become a thriving industrial hub over the last decade, boasting countless national distribution centres. Occupiers are drawn to the area based on its proximity to the Port of Melbourne, the extensive freeway network, competitive leasing rates and booming residential population. Surrounded by built out industrial estates, the Axiom Estate on Robinsons Road has been closely monitored by those looking to secure a premium location. The estate boasts a signalised intersection at its entry, this enables straightforward connectivity to the freeway network located less than 1km* away. 

After the completion of the Western Roads Upgrade Project, Robinsons Road will form part of a 21km north-south route linking the Calder Freeway in the north, down to Sayers Road, Williams Landing. Robinsons Road is now up to six lanes with plans for future expansion again. This road intersects with Ballarat Road, the Western Freeway, Boundary Road, Dohertys Road, Leakes Road and other major east-west linkages.
